{
  "texts": [
    "A systematic review conducted by Albahri et al. (2023) demonstrates trustworthiness and explainability of AI applications in healthcare, incorporating the assessment of quality, bias risk, and data fusion.",
    "Algorithmic fairness involves ensuring that the AI systems give everyone a fair chance and do not unintentionally favor some groups over others or make biased decisions.",
    "It's a critical consideration in the development of CAD models for diseases like AD, as biased predictions can lead to disparities in diagnosis and treatment.",
    "Data scarcity amplifies the challenge of algorithmic fairness because limited data results in misrepresentation of certain demographic groups in the training data, making it difficult for the model to learn unbiased patterns.",
    "A study conducted by Chen et al. (2021) elaborates algorithm fairness in AI in the field of medicine and healthcare."
  ]
}